@Buffalo International. Hazy golden yellow colour, low head, thin body. Taste of malt, hops, citrus. Malty finish. 
Earlier Rating: 7/27/2013 Total Score: 2.9
Pours out of the bottle in a cloudy yellow-golden colour with low head and medium body. Nose of light wheat and hops. Taste of dull hops, wild flowers, wheat, light yeast and leaves. Easy to drink but way nothing special. Nice, but boring and little bit dull.
